r with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Routh was born in 1139, in Watton, Yorkshire, England, his father, Simon De Routh, was 31 and his mother, Matilda, was 29. He married Mathilda De Watton in 1161, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1197, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1139–1197":"1139–1197","1146–1201":"1146–1201","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","1217–1268":"1217–1268","1108–Male":"1108–Surnud","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","1268":"1268","1201":"1201","1146":"1146","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1197":"1197","1161":"1161","1108":"1108","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1139–1197":"1139–1197","1146–1201":"1146–1201","1164–Male":"1164–Kuollut","1217–1268":"1217–1268","1108–Male":"1108–Kuollut","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","1268":"1268","1201":"1201","1146":"1146","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1197":"1197","1161":"1161","1108":"1108","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1139–1197":"1139–1197","1146–1201":"1146–1201","1164–Male":"1164–Décédé","1217–1268":"1217–1268","1108–Male":"1108–Décédé","1110–Female":"1110–Décédée","1217":"1217","1139":"1139","1268":"1268","1201":"1201","1146":"1146","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1197":"1197","1161":"1161","1108":"1108","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William De Routh est né en 1139, à Watton, Everwyck, Angleterre, son pèr